{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fullscreen","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Full screen window covers the entire display area of a screen and has no decorations. The display’s video mode is not changed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Multi-window full-screen mode has a 1px border of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProjectSettings\/rendering\/environment\/defaults\/defaultClearColor"},{"type":"text","text":" color."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"On macOS:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" A new desktop is used to display the running project."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Regardless of the platform, enabling full screen will change the window size to match the monitor’s size. Therefore, make sure your project supports ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"multiple resolutions"},{"type":"text","text":" when enabling full screen mode."}]}],"style":"note","name":"Note"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Window\/Mode-swift.enum\/fullscreen","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"case","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot6WindowC4ModeO10fullscreenyA2EmF","title":"Window.Mode.fullscreen","roleHeading":"Case","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fullscreen","kind":"identifier"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documenta